  <mads:note type="source">"Pomponius, III 5, P. Mela, From Tingentera in southern Spain,
      geographer, 1st century" .....Geographer from Tingentera (Mela 2,96) in southern Spain. Under
      Claudius in AD 43/4 (3,49) he wrote in 3 books the earliest surviving geographical work in
      Latin; the traditional title is De chorographia ('Description of Regions')...." from G&#xE4;rtner,
      Hans Armin (Heidelberg). "Pomponius." Brill's New Pauly. Antiquity volumes edited by: Hubert
      Cancik and Helmuth Schneider . Brill, 2008. Brill Online. Tufts University Library. 04 April
      2008 </mads:note>
  <mads:note type="source">Dictionary of Greek and Roman biography and mythology. By various
      writers. Ed. by William Smith,  1867, Vol 2, pg. 1011:  "Mela, Pomponius, the first Roman
      author who composed a formal, treatise upon Geography....." </mads:note>
